name: Mission Montessori Academy
tweet: Chopsticks, or kuaizi in Chinese, are a pair of small equal-length tapered sticks, usually made of wood, used for eating food. It is believed the first chopsticks were developed over 5,000 years ago in China.

name: Mission Montessori Academy
tweet: The Larkspur Campus has been learning about Chinese culture as we enter the Chinese New Year in the Year of the Rat. The chopsticks definitely tested our students fine-motor skills and dexterity.
